##What will likely be the title of your project?
Maze Game
(Still trying to figure it out)

##In just a sentence or two, summarize your project
The goal of my project is to create a complex maze and have a character programmed to listen to the commands of the player to try and move through the maze.

## In a paragraph or more, detail your project. What will your software do? What features will it have? How will it be executed?
  In the maze game, I am planning on using python and pygame to create a character that will try to get through the maze without knocking into any obstacles or deadends. 
The software will include a game window displaying the maze, a player going through the maze, and game mechanics like a timer and score system. The maze will be designed 
using a data structure such as a 2D array or a graph, and will be drawn on the game window using Pygame's drawing functions. The player character will be controlled by 
the player through keyboard input or mouse control, and will move through the maze to find the correct path to the goal. The game will have obstacles or enemies that the 
player needs to avoid, and collision detection will be implemented to handle collisions between the player and the maze walls or obstacles. The game will also have a 
timer to keep track of the player's time, a score system to track the player's progress, and possibly other game mechanics to add challenge and excitement. 
The game will be executed by running the Python code with Pygame library, which will handle the game window, graphics, user input, and game logic. The player will 
interact with the game through keyboard or mouse input, and the game will provide visual feedback and updates on the screen.

